HEADWORD: Phonics
<hw>Phon"ics</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocr⟧n"⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Same as <er>Phonetics</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A method of teaching reading and spelling to
beginning students, emphasizing the sound values of individual letters
and syllables, and the relationship between pronunciation and spelling.
Contrasted to <contr>whole language method</contr> and <contr>sentence
method</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phono-</ent>⟦br⟧
